WEBVTT

1
00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:35.400
GAME OF THRONES

2
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:39.320
Episode 4

3
00:02:33.640 --> 00:02:35.880
The little lord's
been dreaming again.

4
00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:45.960
- We have visitors.
- I don't want to see anyone.

5
00:02:46.480 --> 00:02:48.880
Really? If I was cooped up
all day with no one

6
00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.160
but this old bat for company.
I'd go mad.

7
00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:55.040
Anyway. you don't have a choice.
Robb's waiting.

8
00:02:55.640 --> 00:02:57.280
I don't want to go.

9
00:02:57.400 --> 00:02:59.800
Neither do I.
But Robb's lord of Winterfell.

10
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:02.920
Which means I do what he says.
and you do what I say.

11
00:03:04.200 --> 00:03:06.040
Hodor!

12
00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:12.920
Help Bran down the hall.

13
00:03:20.560 --> 00:03:23.840
I must say I received a slightly
warmer welcome on my last visit.

14
00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:26.720
Any man of the Night's Watch
is welcome at Winterfell.

15
00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:29.200
Any man of the Night's Watch.
but not I. eh. boy?

16
00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:31.240
I'm not your boy. Lannister.

17
00:03:31.320 --> 00:03:33.720
I'm lord of Winterfell
while my father is away.

18
00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:36.120
Then you might learn
a lord's courtesy.

19
00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:41.040
So it's true.

20
00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:44.040
Hello. Bran.

21
00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:46.960
Do you remember anything
about what happened?

22
00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:49.720
- He has no memory of that day.
- Curious.

23
00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:52.000
Why are you here?

24
00:03:52.760 --> 00:03:55.520
Would your charming companion
be so kind as to kneel?

25
00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:58.160
- My neck is beginning to hurt.
- Kneel. Hodor.

26
00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:05.760
- Do you like to ride. Bran?
- Yes. I mean. I did like to.

27
00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:07.960
The boy has lost
the use of his legs.

28
00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:11.360
What of it? With the right horse
and saddle. even a cripple can ride.

29
00:04:11.440 --> 00:04:13.600
- I'm not a cripple.
- Then I'm not a dwarf.

30
00:04:13.680 --> 00:04:16.600
My father will rejoice to hear it.
I have a gift for you.

31
00:04:18.280 --> 00:04:20.920
Give this to your saddler.
He'll provide the rest.

32
00:04:22.520 --> 00:04:24.560
You must shape the horse
to the rider.

33
00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:27.800
Begin with a yearling and teach it
to respond to the reins

34
00:04:27.880 --> 00:04:30.000
and to the boy's voice.

35
00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:33.000
- Will I really be able to ride?
- You will.

36
00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:35.920
On horseback you will be
as tall as any of them.

37
00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.760
Is this some kind of trick?
Why do you want to help him?

38
00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.680
I have a tender spot in my heart
for cripples and bastards

39
00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:43.760
and broken things.

40
00:04:44.520 --> 00:04:46.440
You've done my brother
a kindness.

41
00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:48.680
The hospitality of Winterfell
is yours.

42
00:04:48.760 --> 00:04:51.280
Spare me your false courtesies.
Lord Stark.

43
00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.960
There's a brothel outside your
walls. I'll find a bed there

44
00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:57.120
and both of us
will sleep easier.

45
00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:04.400
Can't resist some Northern ass?
If you like redheads.

46
00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:06.160
ask for Ros.

47
00:05:06.360 --> 00:05:08.840
Come to see me off. Greyjoy?
Kind of you.

48
00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:11.520
Your master doesn't seem
to like Lannisters.

49
00:05:11.600 --> 00:05:14.080
- He's not my master.
- No. of course not.

50
00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:17.600
What happened here?
Where is Lady Stark?

51
00:05:17.680 --> 00:05:20.360
- Why didn't she receive me?
- She wasn't feeling well.

52
00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:22.880
She's not in Winterfell.
is she? Where did she go?

53
00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:25.000
- My lady's whereabouts...
- My lady?

54
00:05:25.080 --> 00:05:28.080
Your loyalty to your
captors is touching.

55
00:05:28.920 --> 00:05:31.480
Tell me. how do you think
Balon Greyjoy would feel

56
00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:34.320
if he could see that his only
son has turned lackey?

57
00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:38.800
I remember seeing my father's
fleet burn in Lannisport.

58
00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:41.280
I believe your uncles
were responsible?

59
00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:43.080
Must have been
a pretty sight.

60
00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:45.960
Nothing prettier than watching
sailors burn alive.

61
00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:49.920
Yes. a great victory for your people.
Shame how it all turned out.

62
00:05:50.160 --> 00:05:53.360
- We were outnumbered ten to one.
- A stupid rebellion. then.

63
00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:57.600
I suppose you father realized that
when your brothers died in battle.

64
00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:01.040
And now here you are.
your enemies' squire.

65
00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.560
- Careful. Imp.
- I've offended you. Forgive me.

66
00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.840
It's been a rough morning.

67
00:06:07.160 --> 00:06:10.440
Anyway. don't despair.
I'm a constant disappointment

68
00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:13.200
to my own father and I've learned
to live with it.

69
00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:18.600
Your next tumble with Ros is on me.
I'll try not to wear her out.

70
00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:38.920
Left foot forward. Good. Now pivot
as you deliver the stroke.

71
00:06:39.240 --> 00:06:41.040
Put all your weight
behind it.

72
00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:43.120
What in seven hells
is that?

73
00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:46.600
They'll need an eighth hell
to fit him in.

74
00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:50.040
Tell them your name.

75
00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:54.600
Samwell Tarly. of Horn Hill...
I mean I was of Horn Hill. I...

76
00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:59.440
- I've come to take the black.
- Come to take the black pudding.

77
00:07:00.080 --> 00:07:02.400
Well. you couldn't be any worse
than you look.

78
00:07:03.040 --> 00:07:05.560
Rast. see what he can do.

79
00:07:15.400 --> 00:07:17.880
I yield! Please. no more...

80
00:07:18.120 --> 00:07:20.040
On your feet.
Pick up your sword!

81
00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:23.520
Hit him
'til he finds his feet.

82
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:35.840
It seems they've run short
of poachers and thieves down south.

83
00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:38.040
Now they send us
squealing bloody pigs.

84
00:07:38.120 --> 00:07:40.000
Again. Harder.

85
00:07:41.840 --> 00:07:44.680
- I yield...
- Enough! He yielded.

86
00:07:48.200 --> 00:07:50.120
Looks like the bastard's
in love.

87
00:07:52.920 --> 00:07:56.160
All right then. Lord Snow.
you wish to defend your lady love.

88
00:07:56.280 --> 00:07:58.680
let's make an exercise of it.
You two!

89
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:02.200
Three of you ought to be sufficient
to make Lady Piggy squeal.

90
00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:05.840
All you need to do
is get past the bastard.

91
00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:10.400
- You sure you want to do this?
- No.

92
00:08:23.760 --> 00:08:25.280
Yield...

93
00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:27.040
I yield!

94
00:08:28.560 --> 00:08:31.160
We're done for today.
Go clean the armory.

95
00:08:32.080 --> 00:08:34.000
That's all you're good for.

96
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:39.600
- Well fought!
- Piss off.

97
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:46.480
- Did he hurt you?
- I've had worse.

98
00:08:48.360 --> 00:08:50.720
You can call me Sam.
If you want.

99
00:08:51.920 --> 00:08:54.960
- My mother calls me Sam.
- It's not going to get any easier.

100
00:08:55.280 --> 00:08:57.360
You're going to have
to defend yourself.

101
00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.320
Why didn't you get up
and fight?

102
00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:02.320
I wanted to...
I just couldn't.

103
00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:04.480
Why not?

104
00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.240
I'm a coward.

105
00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:12.160
- My father always says so.
- The Wall's no place for cowards.

106
00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:16.360
You're right. I'm sorry. I...
I just wanted to thank you.

107
00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:29.560
A bloody coward.

108
00:09:29.680 --> 00:09:33.200
People saw us talking to him.
Now. they'll think we're cowards too.

109
00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:36.720
- You're too stupid to be a coward.
- You're too stupid to be...

110
00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:38.920
Quick now.
before summer's over.

111
00:10:15.360 --> 00:10:18.120
Vaes Dothrak.
The city of the horselords.

112
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:22.240
A pile of mud.

113
00:10:22.560 --> 00:10:25.280
Mud and shit and twigs.
Best these savages can do.

114
00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:28.800
These are my people now.
You shouldn't call them savages.

115
00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:31.840
I'll call them what I like.
Because they're my people.

116
00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:35.840
This is my army. Drogo is marching
the wrong way with my army.

117
00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:57.840
If my brother was given
an army of Dothraki

118
00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:00.840
could they conquer
the Seven Kingdoms?

119
00:11:02.200 --> 00:11:04.680
The Dothraki have never crossed
the Narrow Sea.

120
00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:07.160
They fear any water
their horses can't drink.

121
00:11:07.240 --> 00:11:09.160
But if they did...

122
00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:12.920
King Robert is fool enough
to meet them in open battle...

123
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:15.520
but the men advising him
are different.

124
00:11:15.600 --> 00:11:17.440
And you know these men?

125
00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:20.560
I fought beside them once.
long ago.

126
00:11:21.880 --> 00:11:25.560
Now Ned Stark wants my head.
He drove me from my land.

127
00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:30.240
You sold slaves.

128
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:33.240
Aye.

129
00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:36.120
Why?

130
00:11:36.200 --> 00:11:38.480
I had no money
and an expensive wife.

131
00:11:39.840 --> 00:11:44.040
- Where is she now?
- In another place. With another man.

132
00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:53.640
- Your grace...
- Yes. my dear.

133
00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:57.040
- They call you the Last Dragon.
- They do.

134
00:12:00.280 --> 00:12:02.880
You have
dragon's blood in your veins?

135
00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:06.600
It's entirely possible.

136
00:12:08.240 --> 00:12:10.000
What happened
to the dragons?

137
00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:12.400
I was told that brave men
killed them all.

138
00:12:15.960 --> 00:12:20.320
The brave men didn't kill dragons.
The brave men rode them.

139
00:12:21.960 --> 00:12:25.000
Rode them from Valyria to build
the greatest civilization

140
00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:27.440
this world has ever seen.

141
00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:31.200
The breath of their greatest
dragon forged the Iron Throne

142
00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:34.520
that the Usurper
is keeping warm for me.

143
00:12:35.920 --> 00:12:39.880
The swords of the vanquished.
a thousand of them...

144
00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:44.320
Melted together
like so many candles.

145
00:12:48.520 --> 00:12:50.760
I've always wanted
to see a dragon.

146
00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:55.600
There is nothing in the world
I'd rather see.

147
00:12:55.880 --> 00:12:59.600
- Really. Why dragons?
- They can fly.

148
00:13:00.800 --> 00:13:03.280
Wherever they are. a few flaps
of their wings

149
00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:06.560
and they're somewhere else.
far away.

150
00:13:10.520 --> 00:13:12.440
And they can kill.

151
00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:16.160
Anyone or anything that tries
to hurt them

152
00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.440
gets burned away to nothing.

153
00:13:23.520 --> 00:13:25.880
Like so many candles.

154
00:13:29.400 --> 00:13:32.640
Seeing a dragon would make me
very happy.

155
00:13:33.760 --> 00:13:35.960
After fifteen years
in the pleasure house.

156
00:13:36.040 --> 00:13:38.400
I suppose just seeing the sky
makes you happy.

157
00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:40.760
I was not locked in.
I have seen things.

158
00:13:40.840 --> 00:13:42.480
What have you seen?

159
00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:46.200
I've seen a man from Asshai
with a dagger of real dragonglass.

160
00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:49.120
And a man who could
change his face

161
00:13:49.240 --> 00:13:51.720
the way other men
change their clothes.

162
00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:56.000
I've seen a pirate who wore
his weight in gold.

163
00:13:57.080 --> 00:14:00.000
whose ship had sails
of colored silk.

164
00:14:02.880 --> 00:14:08.120
- So... have you seen one?
- A pirate ship?

165
00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:10.960
A dragon!

166
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:15.360
No. The last one died long
before I was born.

167
00:14:17.640 --> 00:14:19.640
I'll tell you what I have seen:

168
00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:22.640
their skulls.

169
00:14:23.120 --> 00:14:25.920
They used to decorate the Throne Room
in the Red Keep.

170
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:28.920
When I was very young. three or four.
my father used to walk me

171
00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:31.600
down the rows.
and I'd recite the names for him.

172
00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:34.680
When I got them all right.
he'd give me a sweet.

173
00:14:35.920 --> 00:14:39.160
The ones by the door were the last
ones they'd been able to hatch.

174
00:14:39.240 --> 00:14:42.680
They were stunted and wrong.
no bigger than dog skulls.

175
00:14:44.680 --> 00:14:47.760
But as you got closer
to the Iron Throne.

176
00:14:50.360 --> 00:14:54.120
they got bigger
and bigger and bigger.

177
00:14:57.800 --> 00:15:01.000
There was Ghiscar.
and Valryon.

178
00:15:03.080 --> 00:15:06.320
Vermithrax. Essovius. Archonei...

179
00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:11.200
Meraxes...

180
00:15:13.240 --> 00:15:15.800
Vhagar.

181
00:15:16.920 --> 00:15:19.200
And Balerion the Dread.

182
00:15:19.760 --> 00:15:24.880
Whose fire forged
the seven kingdoms into one.

183
00:15:30.720 --> 00:15:32.760
What happened
to the skulls?

184
00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:39.160
I don't know. The Usurper had them
all smashed to powder. I expect.

185
00:15:40.680 --> 00:15:42.520
Scattered to the winds.

186
00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:48.920
- That's very sad.
- It is.

187
00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:54.760
Why did I buy you?
To make me sad?

188
00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:57.040
No. your grace.

189
00:15:57.720 --> 00:16:00.320
To teach your sister.

190
00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:03.400
To teach my sister how to be
a better lover?

191
00:16:04.040 --> 00:16:06.800
You think I bought you
to make Khal Drogo happy?

192
00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:13.640
You pretty little idiot.

193
00:16:16.160 --> 00:16:18.240
Go ahead. Get on with it.

194
00:16:27.840 --> 00:16:31.960
Someday your husband will sit there
and you will sit by his side.

195
00:16:33.240 --> 00:16:37.000
And one day. before too long. you will
present your son to the court.

196
00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:42.000
All the lords of Westeros will gather
here to see the little prince.

197
00:16:42.400 --> 00:16:44.040
What if I have a girl?

198
00:16:44.200 --> 00:16:47.400
Gods be good. you'll have
boys and girls and plenty of them.

199
00:16:47.720 --> 00:16:50.880
- But what if I only have girls?
- I wouldn't worry about that.

200
00:16:51.960 --> 00:16:54.920
Jeyne Poole's mother had five
children. all of them girls.

201
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:57.640
- Yes. but it's highly unlikely.
- But what if?

202
00:16:59.520 --> 00:17:03.520
Well. if you only had girls.
I suppose the throne would pass

203
00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:05.840
to Prince Joffrey's
little brother.

204
00:17:06.520 --> 00:17:10.200
- And everyone would hate me.
- Nobody could ever hate you.

205
00:17:11.160 --> 00:17:13.080
- Joffrey does.
- Nonsense.

206
00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:15.600
Why would you say such a thing?

207
00:17:17.560 --> 00:17:21.240
That business with the wolves?
Sansa. I've told you a hundred times.

208
00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:24.120
- A direwolf is...
- Please shut up about it.

209
00:17:26.240 --> 00:17:28.000
Do you remember your lessons?

210
00:17:29.960 --> 00:17:33.320
- Who built the Iron Throne?
- Aegon the Conqueror.

211
00:17:34.200 --> 00:17:37.120
- And who built the Red Keep?
- Maegor the Cruel.

212
00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:39.720
And how many years
did it take to...

213
00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:43.000
My grandfather and uncle were
murdered here. weren't they?

214
00:17:43.880 --> 00:17:46.640
They were killed on the orders
of King Aerys. yes.

215
00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:50.440
- The Mad King.
- Commonly known as the Mad King.

216
00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:53.720
Why were they killed?

217
00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:57.440
You should be speak to your father
about these matters.

218
00:17:57.520 --> 00:17:59.600
I don't want to speak
to my father. Ever.

219
00:17:59.680 --> 00:18:03.400
Sansa. You will find it in your heart
to forgive your father.

220
00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:06.800
No I won't.

221
00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:09.960
It's the Hand's tournament
that's causing all this trouble.

222
00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:11.720
The King's tournament.

223
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:14.040
I assure you.
the Hand wants no part of it.

224
00:18:14.680 --> 00:18:17.760
Call it what you will. Lord Stark.
The city's packed with people

225
00:18:17.840 --> 00:18:19.480
and more flooding in
every day.

226
00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:22.720
Last night we had a tavern riot.
a brothel fire. three stabbings

227
00:18:22.800 --> 00:18:25.360
and a drunken horse race
down the Street of Sisters.

228
00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:26.960
Dreadful.

229
00:18:27.040 --> 00:18:29.760
If you can't keep the king's peace.
perhaps the City Watch

230
00:18:29.840 --> 00:18:31.800
should be commanded
by someone who can.

231
00:18:31.880 --> 00:18:33.720
- I need more men.
- You'll get fifty.

232
00:18:33.800 --> 00:18:36.000
- Lord Baelish will see it paid for.
- I will?

233
00:18:36.080 --> 00:18:38.040
You found money
for a champion's purse.

234
00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:41.880
you can find money to keep the peace.
I'll also give you twenty men

235
00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:44.760
from my household guard.
until the crowds have left.

236
00:18:44.920 --> 00:18:47.880
Thank you. my lord Hand. ser.
They'll be put to good use.

237
00:18:50.360 --> 00:18:52.240
The sooner this is over.
the better.

238
00:18:52.320 --> 00:18:54.640
The realm prospers from such
events. my lord.

239
00:18:54.720 --> 00:18:57.400
They bring the great a chance
at glory. and the lowly

240
00:18:57.480 --> 00:18:59.240
a respite from their woes.

241
00:18:59.320 --> 00:19:03.360
And every inn in the city is full. and
the whores are walking bow-legged.

242
00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:06.200
I'm sure the tourney
puts coins in many a pocket.

243
00:19:06.280 --> 00:19:09.480
Now... If there's nothing else.
my lords...

244
00:19:20.800 --> 00:19:23.080
Oh. this heat.
On days like this.

245
00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:26.000
I envy you northerners
for your summer snows.

246
00:19:26.080 --> 00:19:27.960
Until tomorrow my lord...

247
00:19:28.040 --> 00:19:30.560
I've been hoping to talk
with you about Jon Arryn.

248
00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:36.560
Lord Arryn? His death was
a great sadness for all of us.

249
00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:41.320
I took personal charge of his care.
but I could not save him.

250
00:19:43.280 --> 00:19:47.640
His sickness struck him
very hard and very fast.

251
00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:52.440
I had just seen him in my chambers
the night before he passed.

252
00:19:53.120 --> 00:19:55.640
Lord Jon often came to me
for counsel.

253
00:19:56.440 --> 00:19:58.200
Why?

254
00:19:59.280 --> 00:20:01.480
I've been Grand Maester
for many years.

255
00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:05.240
Kings and Hands have come
to me for advice since...

256
00:20:05.320 --> 00:20:07.800
What did Jon want?
The night before he died.

257
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:13.000
- He inquired about a book.
- A book? What book?

258
00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:17.360
I fear you would find it
of little interest.

259
00:20:18.680 --> 00:20:20.560
It's a ponderous tome...

260
00:20:20.680 --> 00:20:23.000
I'd like to read it.

261
00:20:26.760 --> 00:20:31.120
The Lineages and Histories of the
Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms.

262
00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:37.520
With Descriptions of Many
High Lords and Noble Ladies

263
00:20:38.160 --> 00:20:40.160
and Their Children.

264
00:20:57.200 --> 00:21:00.960
Harkon Umber. first of his name.
born to Lord Hother Umber

265
00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:05.080
and Lady Amaryllis Umber in the
183rd year after Aegon's Landing

266
00:21:05.160 --> 00:21:07.120
at the Last Hearth.

267
00:21:07.240 --> 00:21:09.760
Blue of eye. brown of hair
and fair complected.

268
00:21:09.920 --> 00:21:13.960
died in his 14th year of wounds
sustained in a bear hunt.

269
00:21:14.920 --> 00:21:17.480
As I said. my lord.
a ponderous read.

270
00:21:18.040 --> 00:21:20.440
Did Jon Arryn tell you
what he wanted with it?

271
00:21:20.640 --> 00:21:23.160
He did not. my lord.
And I did not presume to ask.

272
00:21:23.440 --> 00:21:25.480
- Jon's death...
- Such a tragedy.

273
00:21:25.560 --> 00:21:28.000
Did he say anything to you
during his final hours?

274
00:21:28.080 --> 00:21:30.160
Nothing of import. my lord.

275
00:21:30.880 --> 00:21:33.440
Well. there was one phrase
he kept repeating.

276
00:21:34.840 --> 00:21:37.520
The seed is strong.
I believe it was.

277
00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:40.600
The seed is strong?
What does that mean?

278
00:21:42.040 --> 00:21:44.760
The dying mind is a demented mind.
Lord Stark.

279
00:21:45.840 --> 00:21:49.280
For all the weight they're given.
last words usually have

280
00:21:49.360 --> 00:21:51.560
as much significance
as first words.

281
00:21:51.640 --> 00:21:54.480
And you're quite certain
he died of a natural illness?

282
00:21:54.680 --> 00:21:56.800
What else could it be?

283
00:21:57.520 --> 00:21:59.320
Poison.

284
00:21:59.720 --> 00:22:01.560
A disturbing thought.

285
00:22:01.640 --> 00:22:05.440
No. I don't think it likely.
The Hand was loved by all.

286
00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:08.000
What sort of man
would dare...

287
00:22:08.080 --> 00:22:10.760
I've heard it said that poison
is a woman's weapon.

288
00:22:11.160 --> 00:22:16.000
Yes. women. cravens...
and eunuchs.

289
00:22:18.160 --> 00:22:20.640
Did you know
that Lord Varys is a eunuch?

290
00:22:21.040 --> 00:22:24.240
- Everybody knows that.
- Yes. yes. of course.

291
00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:28.560
How that sort of person
found himself on the king's council.

292
00:22:28.640 --> 00:22:30.480
I'll never know.

293
00:22:30.560 --> 00:22:33.560
- I've taken enough of your time.
- No trouble at all. my lord.

294
00:22:33.640 --> 00:22:35.760
- It is a great honor...
- Thank you.

295
00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:38.160
I'll find my own way out.

296
00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:03.000
Syrio says a water dancer
can stand on one toe for hours.

297
00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:06.080
It's a hard fall down
these steps.

298
00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:09.920
Syrio says every hurt is a lesson
and every lesson makes you better.

299
00:23:11.520 --> 00:23:13.480
Tomorrow I'm going
to chase cats.

300
00:23:13.800 --> 00:23:16.040
Cats? Syrio says...

301
00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:18.320
He says every swordsman
should study cats.

302
00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:21.040
They're quiet as shadows
and light as feathers.

303
00:23:21.120 --> 00:23:23.200
You have to be
quick to catch them.

304
00:23:23.280 --> 00:23:25.000
Well. he's right
about that.

305
00:23:25.080 --> 00:23:28.160
Now that Bran's awake.
will he come live with us?

306
00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:34.280
He needs to get
his strength back first.

307
00:23:34.480 --> 00:23:36.640
He wants to be a knight
of the King's Guard.

308
00:23:36.920 --> 00:23:38.920
He can't be one now.
can he?

309
00:23:39.640 --> 00:23:45.240
No... But someday he may be
the lord of a holdfast

310
00:23:46.640 --> 00:23:48.360
or sit on the king's council.

311
00:23:49.560 --> 00:23:52.480
Or he might raise castles
like Brandon the Builder.

312
00:23:54.240 --> 00:23:56.080
Can I be lord of a holdfast?

313
00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:03.640
You will marry a high lord
and rule his castle.

314
00:24:05.120 --> 00:24:09.160
and your sons will be knights
and princes and lords.

315
00:24:12.200 --> 00:24:14.040
No.

316
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:17.080
That's not me.

317
00:24:38.720 --> 00:24:40.320
Hello.

318
00:24:41.760 --> 00:24:44.360
Ser Alliser said I'm to be
your new watch partner.

319
00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:49.520
I should warn you.
I don't see all that well.

320
00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:55.480
Come stand by the fire.
It's warmer.

321
00:24:55.880 --> 00:24:59.120
- No. that's all right. I'm fine.
- You're not. you're freezing.

322
00:25:11.280 --> 00:25:13.120
I don't like high places.

323
00:25:13.760 --> 00:25:16.200
You can't fight. You can't see.

324
00:25:17.680 --> 00:25:20.880
You're afraid of heights.
and animals. and everything else.

325
00:25:22.280 --> 00:25:24.320
What are you doing here. Sam?

326
00:25:28.400 --> 00:25:31.240
On the morning of my 18th nameday.
my father came to me.

327
00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:34.720
You're almost a man now.
he said.

328
00:25:36.320 --> 00:25:38.720
but you're not worthy
of my land and title.

329
00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:42.760
Tomorrow. you're going
to take the black.

330
00:25:43.040 --> 00:25:45.840
forsake all claim to your
inheritance and start north.

331
00:25:47.040 --> 00:25:49.400
If you do not. he said.

332
00:25:51.360 --> 00:25:53.320
then we'll have a hunt.

333
00:25:53.760 --> 00:25:56.600
And somewhere in these woods
your horse will stumble.

334
00:25:56.840 --> 00:25:59.480
and you'll be thrown from
your saddle to die...

335
00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:05.400
or so I'll tell your mother.
Nothing would please me more.

336
00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:14.680
Lord Alliser is going to make me
fight again tomorrow. isn't he?

337
00:26:15.440 --> 00:26:17.440
Yes. He is.

338
00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:20.080
I'm not going to get
any better. you know.

339
00:26:21.320 --> 00:26:24.040
Well...
you can't get any worse.

340
00:26:34.440 --> 00:26:36.360
I hear you're reading
a boring book.

341
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:41.280
- Pycelle talks too much.
- Oh. he never stops.

342
00:26:42.600 --> 00:26:44.480
Do you know
Ser Hugh of the Vale?

343
00:26:46.040 --> 00:26:49.000
Not surprising. Until recently.
he was only a squire.

344
00:26:49.640 --> 00:26:51.600
Jon Arryn's squire.

345
00:26:52.120 --> 00:26:55.920
He was knighted almost immediately
after his master's untimely death.

346
00:26:56.240 --> 00:26:58.160
Knighted for what?

347
00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:02.520
- Why are you telling me this?
- I promised Cat I'd help you.

348
00:27:03.120 --> 00:27:05.880
Where is Ser Hugh?
I'll speak to him.

349
00:27:06.160 --> 00:27:08.520
A singularly bad idea.
Do you see that boy?

350
00:27:10.320 --> 00:27:12.240
One of Varys's little birds.

351
00:27:12.560 --> 00:27:16.000
The Spider has taken a great interest
in your comings and goings.

352
00:27:16.200 --> 00:27:19.280
Now look there.
That one belongs to the Queen.

353
00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:24.400
And do you that one pretending
to read her book?

354
00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:28.080
- Varys or the Queen?
- No. she's one of mine.

355
00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:33.960
Is there someone in your service
that you trust completely?

356
00:27:35.760 --> 00:27:37.320
Yes.

357
00:27:37.440 --> 00:27:39.480
The wiser answer was no.
my lord.

358
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:43.480
Get a message to this paragon
of yours discreetly.

359
00:27:44.280 --> 00:27:47.040
send him to question
Ser Hugh. After that.

360
00:27:47.160 --> 00:27:50.120
you might want him to visit
a certain armorer in the city.

361
00:27:50.760 --> 00:27:53.640
He lives in a large house at the
top of the Street of Steel.

362
00:27:53.720 --> 00:27:55.520
- Why?
- I have my observers.

363
00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:59.080
And it's possible they saw
Lord Arryn visit this armorer

364
00:27:59.160 --> 00:28:01.640
several times
in the weeks before his death.

365
00:28:03.800 --> 00:28:06.480
Lord Baelish. Perhaps I was wrong
to distrust you.

366
00:28:06.720 --> 00:28:09.120
Distrusting me was the wisest
thing you've done

367
00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:11.400
since you climbed off
your horse.

368
00:28:25.400 --> 00:28:27.280
Ser Hugh...

369
00:28:27.640 --> 00:28:29.800
- Ser Hugh?
- As you can see. I'm busy.

370
00:28:30.280 --> 00:28:32.480
I'm here on behalf
of Lord Eddard Stark.

371
00:28:32.960 --> 00:28:36.000
the Hand of the King.
I'm the captain of his guard.

372
00:28:36.640 --> 00:28:38.560
I didn't catch
your name. Ser...

373
00:28:38.760 --> 00:28:40.920
No Ser...
I'm not a knight.

374
00:28:41.040 --> 00:28:43.760
I see. Well.
it so happens that I am.

375
00:28:49.280 --> 00:28:51.760
He said he'd be glad to talk
to the Hand himself.

376
00:28:51.960 --> 00:28:53.560
He's a knight. you see.

377
00:28:53.640 --> 00:28:57.520
Ah. a knight. They strut around
like roosters down here.

378
00:28:58.760 --> 00:29:01.560
Even the ones who've never seen
an arrow coming their way.

379
00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:03.400
You shouldn't be out here.
my lord.

380
00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:05.480
There no saying
who has eyes where.

381
00:29:05.560 --> 00:29:07.320
Let them look.

382
00:29:08.560 --> 00:29:11.320
The former Hand did call on me.
my lord. several times.

383
00:29:11.400 --> 00:29:13.960
But he did not honor me
with his patronage.

384
00:29:14.880 --> 00:29:18.080
- What did Lord Arryn want?
- He always came to see the boy.

385
00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:21.600
- I'd like to see him as well.
- As you wish. my lord.

386
00:29:23.120 --> 00:29:25.000
Gendry!

387
00:29:28.720 --> 00:29:31.760
Here he is. Strong for his age.
Works hard.

388
00:29:33.680 --> 00:29:35.840
Show the Hand
the helmet you made. lad.

389
00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:51.160
- This is fine work.
- It's not for sale.

390
00:29:51.240 --> 00:29:54.440
Boy. this is the King's Hand!
If his lordship wants the helm...

391
00:29:54.520 --> 00:29:56.680
I made it for me.

392
00:29:56.960 --> 00:29:59.680
- Forgive him. my lord.
- There's nothing to forgive.

393
00:30:00.680 --> 00:30:03.760
When Lord Arryn came to visit you.
what would you talk about?

394
00:30:04.400 --> 00:30:06.360
He asked me questions
is all. m'lord.

395
00:30:06.440 --> 00:30:08.600
What kind of questions?

396
00:30:10.280 --> 00:30:13.520
About my work at first.
how I was treated.

397
00:30:13.600 --> 00:30:15.640
if I liked it here...

398
00:30:18.000 --> 00:30:20.160
Then he started asking
about my mother.

399
00:30:20.560 --> 00:30:22.360
Your mother?

400
00:30:22.520 --> 00:30:24.480
Who she was.
what she looked like.

401
00:30:24.760 --> 00:30:26.720
And what did you tell him?

402
00:30:27.880 --> 00:30:30.000
She died when I was little.

403
00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:34.120
She had yellow hair...
Sometimes she'd sing to me...

404
00:30:38.720 --> 00:30:40.480
Look at me.

405
00:30:50.120 --> 00:30:51.960
Go back to work. lad.

406
00:30:53.720 --> 00:30:56.720
If the day ever comes when that boy
would rather wield a sword

407
00:30:56.800 --> 00:30:59.320
than forge one.
send him to me.

408
00:31:04.040 --> 00:31:05.840
Find anything?

409
00:31:07.160 --> 00:31:09.040
King Robert's bastard son.

410
00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:18.640
A message for the king
from Lord Stark.

411
00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:22.160
Should I leave it with...

412
00:31:22.800 --> 00:31:24.600
Listen.

413
00:31:25.280 --> 00:31:27.040
Do you hear them?

414
00:31:29.320 --> 00:31:31.680
How many do you think are
in there with him?

415
00:31:33.560 --> 00:31:36.680
- Guess.
- Three. Four.

416
00:31:38.880 --> 00:31:40.800
He likes to do this
when I'm on duty.

417
00:31:41.480 --> 00:31:43.720
Makes me listen as he insults
my sister.

418
00:31:49.240 --> 00:31:51.960
- Forgive me. my lord...
- Why? Have you wronged me?

419
00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:57.800
- We've met before. you know.
- Have we? Strange I've forgotten.

420
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:02.000
At the Siege of Pyke. We fought side
by side one afternoon.

421
00:32:04.080 --> 00:32:06.200
- Is that where you got your scar?
- Aye.

422
00:32:07.440 --> 00:32:09.440
One of the Greyjoys
nearly took my eye.

423
00:32:09.640 --> 00:32:12.280
- Ornery sons of whores.
- They like their bloodshed.

424
00:32:12.360 --> 00:32:16.040
They stopped liking it by the end.
That was a proper battle.

425
00:32:17.320 --> 00:32:20.440
You remember Thoros of Myr
charging through the breach?

426
00:32:20.640 --> 00:32:23.680
With his burning sword?
I'll remember that til the day I die.

427
00:32:24.560 --> 00:32:27.240
I saw the youngest Greyjoy lad
at Winterfell.

428
00:32:27.640 --> 00:32:29.960
It's like seeing a shark
on a mountain top.

429
00:32:30.360 --> 00:32:32.920
- Theon? He's a good lad.
- I doubt it.

430
00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:40.320
I bet you smell
like blackberry jam!

431
00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:42.680
Let me smell it! Come here!

432
00:32:44.760 --> 00:32:47.720
Could I leave this with you?
A message from Lord Stark.

433
00:32:47.840 --> 00:32:50.080
I don't serve Lord Stark.

434
00:33:12.520 --> 00:33:15.240
- Where have you been?
- Watch duty. With Sam.

435
00:33:15.760 --> 00:33:17.760
Ah. Prince Porkchop!
Where is he?

436
00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:19.920
- He wasn't hungry.
- Impossible.

437
00:33:20.920 --> 00:33:22.720
That's enough.

438
00:33:28.560 --> 00:33:30.720
Sam's no different
from the rest of us.

439
00:33:31.600 --> 00:33:34.480
There was no place for him
in the world. so he's come here.

440
00:33:35.040 --> 00:33:37.760
We're not going to hurt him
in the training yard anymore.

441
00:33:37.840 --> 00:33:40.040
Never again.
No matter what Thorne says.

442
00:33:40.240 --> 00:33:42.840
He's our brother now
and we're going to protect him.

443
00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:45.160
You are in love. Lord Snow.

444
00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:51.560
You girls do as you please.
but if Thorne sends me

445
00:33:51.680 --> 00:33:55.040
against Lady Piggy. I'm gonna
slice me off a side of bacon.

446
00:34:17.160 --> 00:34:19.360
No one touches Sam.

447
00:34:33.720 --> 00:34:35.520
What are you waiting for?

448
00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:46.640
Attack him!

449
00:34:56.160 --> 00:34:57.960
You! Get in there.

450
00:35:02.760 --> 00:35:04.560
Hit me.

451
00:35:05.640 --> 00:35:07.400
Go on. hit me!

452
00:35:09.480 --> 00:35:11.240
I yield!

453
00:35:11.960 --> 00:35:13.680
I yield!

454
00:35:18.640 --> 00:35:20.560
You think this is funny?

455
00:35:24.680 --> 00:35:28.200
When you're out there beyond the Wall
and the sun is going down.

456
00:35:29.320 --> 00:35:32.240
do you want a man at your back?
Or a sniveling boy?

457
00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:49.440
You send this whore
to give me commands?

458
00:35:49.720 --> 00:35:51.800
I should have sent you
back her head!

459
00:35:52.160 --> 00:35:54.360
Forgive me. khaleesi.
I did as you asked...

460
00:35:54.440 --> 00:35:57.320
Hush now. it's all right.
Irri. take her and leave us.

461
00:35:57.600 --> 00:35:59.360
Yes. khaleesi.

462
00:36:02.200 --> 00:36:03.600
Why did you hit her?!

463
00:36:03.680 --> 00:36:05.440
How many times
do I have to tell you?

464
00:36:05.520 --> 00:36:08.160
- You do not command me.
- I wasn't commanding you!

465
00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:10.280
I just wanted to invite you
to supper.

466
00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:12.280
- What's this?
- It's a gift.

467
00:36:12.360 --> 00:36:14.120
I had it made for you.

468
00:36:14.240 --> 00:36:16.480
Dothraki rags. Are you
going to dress me now?

469
00:36:16.560 --> 00:36:19.240
- Please...
- This stinks of manure. All of it.

470
00:36:19.320 --> 00:36:21.360
Stop! Stop it!

471
00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:23.360
You'd turn me into one
of them. wouldn't you?

472
00:36:23.440 --> 00:36:25.120
Next you'll want
to braid my hair.

473
00:36:25.200 --> 00:36:28.080
You have no right to a braid.
You've won no victories yet.

474
00:36:28.160 --> 00:36:30.640
You don't talk back to me!

475
00:36:32.240 --> 00:36:35.960
You're a horselord's slut
and now you've woken the dragon.

476
00:36:41.840 --> 00:36:44.560
I am a khaleesi of the Dothraki.

477
00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:49.040
I am the wife of the Great Khal
and I carry his son inside me.

478
00:36:50.200 --> 00:36:53.040
The next time you raise
a hand to me

479
00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:56.440
will be the last time
you have hands.

480
00:37:04.440 --> 00:37:07.960
I know for a fact some of the officers
go to that brothel in Mole's Town.

481
00:37:08.040 --> 00:37:09.840
I wouldn't doubt it.

482
00:37:10.280 --> 00:37:13.440
You don't think it's a little unfair?
Making us take our vows

483
00:37:13.520 --> 00:37:16.200
while they sneak off
for a little Sally on the side?

484
00:37:17.560 --> 00:37:19.760
- Sally on the side?
- It's silly. isn't it?

485
00:37:19.840 --> 00:37:22.640
We can't defend the Wall
unless we're celibate?

486
00:37:23.560 --> 00:37:25.280
It's absurd.

487
00:37:25.400 --> 00:37:27.560
I didn't think you'd be
so upset about it.

488
00:37:28.960 --> 00:37:32.600
- Why not? Because I'm fat?
- No.

489
00:37:32.880 --> 00:37:34.880
I like girls
just as much as you do.

490
00:37:36.720 --> 00:37:38.560
They might not like me as much.

491
00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:43.200
I've never been with one.

492
00:37:45.360 --> 00:37:48.120
- You've probably had hundreds.
- No.

493
00:37:51.040 --> 00:37:54.280
As a matter of fact.
I'm the same as you.

494
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:58.280
I find that hard to believe.

495
00:37:59.200 --> 00:38:01.080
I came very close once.

496
00:38:01.880 --> 00:38:04.400
I was alone in a room
with a naked girl. but...

497
00:38:05.720 --> 00:38:08.560
- You didn't know where to put it?
- I know where to put it.

498
00:38:09.440 --> 00:38:11.800
Was she old and ugly?

499
00:38:13.920 --> 00:38:15.640
Young and gorgeous.

500
00:38:17.160 --> 00:38:19.000
A whore named Ros.

501
00:38:20.960 --> 00:38:23.320
- What color hair?
- Red.

502
00:38:24.080 --> 00:38:26.040
I like red hair.

503
00:38:26.720 --> 00:38:28.440
And her...

504
00:38:28.920 --> 00:38:30.720
her...

505
00:38:30.920 --> 00:38:32.480
You don't want to know.

506
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.440
- That good?
- Better.

507
00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:40.600
Why exactly did you not make love
to Ros with the perfect...

508
00:38:43.280 --> 00:38:45.440
- What's my name?
- Jon Snow.

509
00:38:47.440 --> 00:38:49.400
And why is my surname Snow?

510
00:38:50.640 --> 00:38:54.040
Because... you're
a bastard from the North.

511
00:38:56.600 --> 00:39:00.440
I never met my mother. My father
won't even tell me her name.

512
00:39:02.080 --> 00:39:04.000
I don't know
if she's living or dead.

513
00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:09.560
I don't know if she's a noblewoman
or a fisherman's wife.

514
00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:13.560
Or a whore.

515
00:39:15.800 --> 00:39:19.960
So I sat there in the brothel.
as Ros took off her clothes.

516
00:39:22.480 --> 00:39:26.280
But I couldn't do it.
Because all I coud think was.

517
00:39:27.680 --> 00:39:29.880
what if I get her pregnant?

518
00:39:30.200 --> 00:39:33.840
And she has a child.
another bastard named Snow.

519
00:39:39.320 --> 00:39:41.240
It's not a good life
for a child.

520
00:39:46.800 --> 00:39:50.040
So you didn't know
where to put it.

521
00:39:56.720 --> 00:39:58.480
Enjoying yourselves?

522
00:40:00.480 --> 00:40:02.280
You look cold.

523
00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:05.520
It is a bit nippy.

524
00:40:06.080 --> 00:40:10.640
Yes. by the fire.
indoors. it's still summer.

525
00:40:12.520 --> 00:40:14.720
Do you boys even remember
the last winter?

526
00:40:16.240 --> 00:40:18.400
How long has it been now.
ten years?

527
00:40:20.080 --> 00:40:21.840
I remember.

528
00:40:22.040 --> 00:40:24.760
Was it uncomfortable. at Winterfell?
Were there days

529
00:40:24.840 --> 00:40:28.800
