to attack Eastwatch.

535
00:40:46.240 --> 00:40:48.560
So we went looking for some
of his men.

536
00:40:49.080 --> 00:40:51.160
Catch them.
gather some knowledge.

537
00:40:51.560 --> 00:40:54.360
The wildlings who fight
for Mance Rayder are hard men.

538
00:40:54.920 --> 00:40:56.800
Harder than you'll ever be.

539
00:40:57.160 --> 00:40:59.440
They know their country
better than we do.

540
00:40:59.720 --> 00:41:03.760
They knew about the storm coming in.
so they hid in their caves

541
00:41:04.040 --> 00:41:08.440
and waited for it to pass.
We got caught in the open.

542
00:41:10.080 --> 00:41:14.840
Wind so strong it yanked hundred-foot
trees from the ground. roots and all.

543
00:41:15.920 --> 00:41:18.600
You took off your gloves to find
your cock for a piss.

544
00:41:18.680 --> 00:41:20.840
ended up losing a finger
to the frost.

545
00:41:21.720 --> 00:41:23.800
All this in darkness.

546
00:41:26.600 --> 00:41:29.480
You don't know cold.
Neither of you.

547
00:41:33.360 --> 00:41:35.120
The horses died first.

548
00:41:37.760 --> 00:41:40.480
We didn't have enough to feed
them. to keep them warm.

549
00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:44.840
The horses were easy to eat.

550
00:41:47.280 --> 00:41:52.120
But later. when we started
to fall... that wasn't easy.

551
00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:57.480
Shame we didn't have any boys
like you along.

552
00:42:02.560 --> 00:42:04.520
Soft. fat boys like you.

553
00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:08.320
We could have lasted a fortnight
on you and still had bones

554
00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.520
left over for soup.

555
00:42:12.760 --> 00:42:16.520
Soon we'll have new recruits.
And you lot will be passed along

556
00:42:16.600 --> 00:42:19.720
