for assignment.

557
00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:23.840
They'll call you men
of the Night's Watch.

558
00:42:25.240 --> 00:42:27.160
but you'll be fools
to believe it.

559
00:42:28.400 --> 00:42:32.320
You're boys still. and when the winter
comes you'll die...

560
00:42:34.960 --> 00:42:36.680
like flies.

561
00:42:43.280 --> 00:42:44.960
I hit him.

562
00:42:45.480 --> 00:42:47.120
I hit the dragon.

563
00:42:47.200 --> 00:42:49.440
Your brother Rhaegar
was the last dragon.

564
00:42:49.520 --> 00:42:51.960
Viserys is less
than the shadow of a snake.

565
00:42:52.040 --> 00:42:54.360
- He is still the true king.
- The truth now.

566
00:42:56.000 --> 00:42:59.000
Do you want to see your brother
sitting on the Iron Throne?

567
00:42:59.720 --> 00:43:01.600
No.

568
00:43:02.040 --> 00:43:04.400
But the common people
are waiting for him.

569
00:43:04.480 --> 00:43:06.800
Illyrio said they were
sewing dragon banners

570
00:43:06.880 --> 00:43:08.600
and praying for his return.

571
00:43:08.680 --> 00:43:12.560
The common people pray for rain.
health and a summer that never ends.

572
00:43:13.040 --> 00:43:15.600
They don't care what games
the high lords play.

573
00:43:16.400 --> 00:43:18.440
What do you pray for.
Ser Jorah?

574
00:43:22.480 --> 00:43:24.200
Home.

575
00:43:25.400 --> 00:43:27.480
I pray for home. too.

576
00:43:30.800 --> 00:43:33.520
My brother will never take back
the Seven Kingdoms.

577
00:43:35.160 --> 00:43:38.120
He couldn't lead an army even if
my husband gave him one.

578
00:43:41.560 --> 00:43:43.760
He'll never take us home.

579
00:44:02.960 --> 00:44:06.120
- A lover's quarrel?
- I'm sorry? Do I...

580
00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:09.360
Sansa. dear.
this is Lord Baelish. He's...

581
00:44:09.440 --> 00:44:11.480
An old friend of the family.

582
00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:14.280
I've known your mother
a long. long time.

583
00:44:14.360 --> 00:44:16.280
Why do they call you
Littlefinger?

584
00:44:16.360 --> 00:44:18.720
- Don't be rude.
- No. it's quite all right.

585
00:44:20.000 --> 00:44:21.800
I was small as a child.

586
00:44:23.200 --> 00:44:25.880
And I come from a little spit
of land called the Fingers.

587
00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:28.840
So you see. it's an exceedingly
clever nickname.

588
00:44:29.760 --> 00:44:31.640
I've been sitting here
for days.

589
00:44:32.440 --> 00:44:35.040
Start the damned joust
before I piss myself.

590
00:44:43.400 --> 00:44:45.240
Gods. who is that?

591
00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:49.560
Ser Gregor Clegane.
They call him the Mountain.

592
00:44:52.040 --> 00:44:55.320
- The Hound's older brother.
- And his opponent?

593
00:44:56.320 --> 00:44:59.000
Ser Hugh of the Vale.
He was Jon Arryn's squire.

594
00:44:59.880 --> 00:45:01.520
Look how far he's come.

595
00:45:01.640 --> 00:45:04.240
Yes. enough of the bloody pomp.
Have at it!

596
00:46:22.400 --> 00:46:24.400
Not what
you were expecting?

597
00:46:27.720 --> 00:46:30.800
Has anyone told you the story
of the Mountain and the Hound?

598
00:46:32.480 --> 00:46:34.680
Lovely little tale
of brotherly love.

599
00:46:36.600 --> 00:46:40.160
The Hound was just a pup.
six years old. maybe.

600
00:46:41.480 --> 00:46:44.360
Gregor a few years older.
already a big lad.

601
00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:46.840
already getting a bit
of a reputation.

602
00:46:47.240 --> 00:46:50.960
Some lucky boys are born
with a talent for violence.

603
00:46:53.360 --> 00:46:56.080
One evening Gregor found
his little brother

604
00:46:56.360 --> 00:47:02.280
playing with a toy by the fire.
Gregor's toy. a wooden knight.

605
00:47:03.960 --> 00:47:07.360
Gregor didn't say a word.
just grabbed his brother

606
00:47:07.880 --> 00:47:11.400
