his face into the burning coals.

607
00:47:12.160 --> 00:47:16.680
Held him there while the boy
screamed. while his face melted.

608
00:47:22.240 --> 00:47:24.280
Very few people
know that story.

609
00:47:25.600 --> 00:47:27.520
I won't tell anyone.
I promise.

610
00:47:27.840 --> 00:47:30.960
Please don't. If the Hound
ever heard you mention it.

611
00:47:32.040 --> 00:47:34.280
I'm afraid all the knights
in King's Landing

612
00:47:34.360 --> 00:47:36.560
wouldn't be able to save you.

613
00:47:48.880 --> 00:47:51.120
My lord:
Her grace. the Queen.

614
00:47:54.800 --> 00:47:56.320
Your grace.

615
00:47:56.400 --> 00:47:58.160
You're missing
your tournament.

616
00:47:58.240 --> 00:48:00.520
Putting my name on it doesn't
make it mine.

617
00:48:01.880 --> 00:48:05.080
I thought we might put what happened
on the Kingsroad behind us.

618
00:48:05.160 --> 00:48:07.240
The ugliness with the wolves.

619
00:48:09.400 --> 00:48:11.680
Forcing you to kill the beast
was extreme.

620
00:48:12.680 --> 00:48:16.080
Sometimes we go to extremes
where our children are concerned.

621
00:48:17.360 --> 00:48:20.480
- How is Sansa?
- She likes it here.

622
00:48:21.320 --> 00:48:23.200
She's the only Stark
who does.

623
00:48:23.800 --> 00:48:26.880
She favors her mother. There's
not much of the north in her.

624
00:48:26.960 --> 00:48:29.600
- Why are you here?
- I could ask the same of you.

625
00:48:30.440 --> 00:48:32.400
What do you hope
to accomplish?

626
00:48:32.600 --> 00:48:35.160
The king called on me to serve him.
and the realm.

627
00:48:35.440 --> 00:48:38.040
And that's what I'll do
until he tells me otherwise.

628
00:48:38.120 --> 00:48:40.320
You can't help him.
You can't change him.

629
00:48:40.400 --> 00:48:42.960
He'll do what he wants.
which is all he's ever done.

630
00:48:43.040 --> 00:48:45.560
and you'll try your best
to pick up the pieces.

631
00:48:45.680 --> 00:48:48.080
If that's my job.
then so be it.

632
00:48:49.880 --> 00:48:53.760
You're just a soldier. aren't you?
You take your orders and you carry on.

633
00:48:56.080 --> 00:48:57.920
I suppose it makes sense.

634
00:48:58.000 --> 00:49:01.360
Your older brother was trained
to lead. You were trained to follow.

635
00:49:01.440 --> 00:49:04.000
I was also trained to kill
my enemies. your grace.

636
00:49:07.120 --> 00:49:08.880
As was I.

637
00:49:26.840 --> 00:49:28.760
Seven blessings to you.
goodfolk!

638
00:49:29.400 --> 00:49:30.920
And to you.

639
00:49:31.000 --> 00:49:32.880
Boy! Bread. meat and beer.
Quickly.

640
00:49:32.960 --> 00:49:35.200
Good thinking. grandfather.
I'm starving.

641
00:49:35.440 --> 00:49:37.000
A song while we wait?

642
00:49:37.080 --> 00:49:38.880
I'd sooner
throw myself down a well.

643
00:49:38.960 --> 00:49:41.080
Grandfather. this may be
your last chance.

644
00:49:41.160 --> 00:49:44.240
if you're heading North. The only
music those northerners know

645
00:49:44.320 --> 00:49:46.200
is the howling of wolves!

646
00:49:48.520 --> 00:49:51.000
I'm sorry m'lord. we're full up.
Every room...

647
00:49:51.320 --> 00:49:53.520
My men will sleep in the stable.
As for myself

648
00:49:53.600 --> 00:49:55.600
I don't require a large room.

649
00:49:56.040 --> 00:49:58.240
Truly. m'lord.
we have nothing.

650
00:49:58.760 --> 00:50:01.960
Is there nothing I can do
to remedy this?

651
00:50:03.520 --> 00:50:06.400
- You can have my room.
- Now there's a clever man!

652
00:50:08.280 --> 00:50:09.960
You can manage food. I trust?

653
00:50:10.040 --> 00:50:11.800
- Yoren. dine with me.
- Aye. m'lord.

654
00:50:11.880 --> 00:50:15.120
My lord of Lannister! Might I
entertain you while you eat?

655
00:50:15.240 --> 00:50:18.080
I can sing of your father's
victory at King's Landing!

656
00:50:18.160 --> 00:50:20.600
Nothing would be more likely
to ruin my supper.

657
00:50:21.600 --> 00:50:24.920
Lady Stark.
what an unexpected pleasure.

658
00:50:26.600 --> 00:50:28.720
I was sorry to miss you
at Winterfell.

659
00:50:29.120 --> 00:50:31.000
Lady Stark?

660
00:50:38.440 --> 00:50:41.480
I was still Catelyn Tully
the last time I stayed here.

661
00:50:45.240 --> 00:50:49.360
You. sir... Is that the black bat
of Harrenhal

662
00:50:49.640 --> 00:50:51.480
I see embroidered
on your coat?

663
00:50:52.440 --> 00:50:54.160
It is. my lady.

664
00:50:54.240 --> 00:50:57.200
And is Lady Whent a true and honest
friend to my father.

665
00:50:58.000 --> 00:51:00.360
Lord Hoster Tully
of Riverrun?

666
00:51:00.520 --> 00:51:02.600
She is.

667
00:51:04.120 --> 00:51:07.120
The red stallion was always
a welcome sight in Riverrun.

668
00:51:07.480 --> 00:51:10.080
My father counts Jonas Bracken
among his oldest

669
00:51:10.160 --> 00:51:12.280
and most loyal bannermen.

670
00:51:12.800 --> 00:51:14.800
Our lord is honored
by his trust.

671
00:51:15.320 --> 00:51:18.200
I envy your father for all
his fine friends. Lady Stark.

672
00:51:18.280 --> 00:51:21.080
but I don't quite see
the purpose of this.

673
00:51:23.120 --> 00:51:26.880
I know your sigil as well:
the twin towers of Frey.

674
00:51:28.640 --> 00:51:30.640
How fares your lord. sers?

675
00:51:31.440 --> 00:51:34.720
Lord Walder is well. my lady.
He has asked your father to honor him

676
00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:38.280
with his presence on his 90th nameday.
He plans to take another wife.

677
00:51:45.800 --> 00:51:51.560
This man came into my house
as a guest. and there conspired

678
00:51:51.920 --> 00:51:55.640
